<section>

<p>You've reached the <a href="http://npolar.no">Norwegian Polar Institute</a>'s <abbr title="Application Programming Interface">API</abbr> - a searchable data storage service.
{{!--Non-developers should probably head over to the <a href="http://data.npolar.no">Norwegian Polar Data Centre</a>.--}}</p>

<p>The API has a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Representational_state_transfer">REST</a>-style architecture,
where individual documents are identified, retrieved and updated via HTTP requests to a persistent web address, the document URI.</p>

<p><a href="https://github.com/npolar/api.npolar.no">Source</a> is on <a href="https://github.com/">GitHub</a>, see the project <a href="https://github.com/npolar/api.npolar.no/blob/master/README.md#readme">README</a> for more information.</p>

